HEADWORD: Pampero
<hw>Pam*pe"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., fr.
<ets>pampa</ets> a plain.]</ety> <def>A violent wind from the west or
southwest, which sweeps over the pampas of South America and the
adjacent seas, often doing great damage.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Parish.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pamperos</ent>⟦br⟧
